        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="561" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <head>No. 561.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S.
                                    Sackville West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-03-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 19.</date>
                                (Received March 20.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the
                            Marquis of Salisbury has requested me, by telegraph, to represent to you
                            the very great importance which Her Majesty’s Government attach to the
                            presence of a delegate from the United States Government at the
                            approaching sugar conference which opens on the 5th April next, and that
                            the negotiations can not be carried to a successful issue unless the
                            United States take part in them.</p>
                <p>Trusting that you will give this matter your early attention,</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">L. S. Sackville
                                    West.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
